This paper introduces a language for describing stochastic generative processes, which is relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the implementation of query on any Church program using Monte Carlo techniques, which is related to probabilistic programming and computational statistics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper also discusses planning by inference, which is related to control systems and robotics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses non-parametric clustering models, which is related to data mining and machine learning, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
